# example-2
>M01913_157_000000000-AC0PK_1_1106_19388_21464_sense_N_0_1
GAATCGCCGTGTTGTTGCAACCTCCAATCTTGTGCCGTTCGCCCTTCAGTTTGTCGATCATCACTGGAAGTGTTTAGGCTCCGTCCAGATCCAAAGATCGACAGAGTTCCAAGCGACGGGGCGGCAATCCTTCAAACTGAAACCAGAAACTAAACCTACGAATACTAGCGATAGACCATACACATACA
----------------------------------------------------........G.................................................G.............................................................................



1. I should take into account where the 1st nt of the read starts from and where it ends.

Even if I have many '-' at the beginning of the alignment, these do not indicate any deletion
unless they follow at least 1 already aligned nt of the read!
Similary, if many '-' are flanking at the 5' end of the alignment without any other nts following
these should not be considered as deletions of course.
===> check read


2. If there are too many mismatches (e.g. > 10) then I should discard this read as non-aligned.
===> check alignment notation line


3. I should check the amplicon aligned sequence. 
If I have any '-' these indicate insertion, and I should record this information (positions of '-')
===> check amplicon
[ If I have too many insertions I should *discard* this read too]













